headline: Here's Why Shares in Stanley Black & Decker Soared This Week
summary: An improving trading relationship between the U.S. and China is good news for Stanley Black & Decker.  Stanley Black & Decker (NYSE: SWK) stock rose by 12.8% in the week to Friday morning.  The move comes as a thawing in the U.S./China trading relationship encouraged investors to price in a better outcome for the toolmaker's earnings in 2025 and beyond.
